23/02/2010
KABUL, Afghanistan -- A Romanian soldier was killed in Afghanistan on Tuesday (February 23rd), and another was injured when their vehicle struck an explosive device in the Zabul province. 
Romania has around 1,020 troops in Afghanistan. 
Late last month, Bucharest decided to add 600 more troops to the mission. 
(AFP, AP, Mediafax - 23/02/10)
